   rev:'Strings attached, power imbalance, stinginess, one-sided giving, withholding, bad debt',
   meaning:'The Six of Pentacles shows a wealthy figure holding balanced scales in one hand while giving coins to those kneeling before him. The scales are everything in this card — this isn\'t just charity, it\'s fairness. It\'s the understanding that what flows out will flow back, that generosity is its own kind of investment, and that the wheel of fortune can turn for anyone at any time.',
