   rev:'Impatience, wasted effort, lack of results, poor investment, cutting corners, giving up too soon',
   meaning:'The Seven of Pentacles shows a farmer leaning on his hoe, pausing to look at seven pentacles growing from his vines. He\'s tired. He\'s been tending this for a long time. And the harvest isn\'t quite ready yet. This card is the quiet, unglamorous middle of the long game — the part where you\'ve done the work, planted the seeds, and now you have to wait.',
   practical:'You\'re in the long game right now — and that\'s exactly where you\'re supposed to be. Don\'t pull the plant up to check if the roots are growing. Trust the process, stay consistent, and resist the urge to abandon what you\'ve been building.',
